The paper deals with blind channel identification and signal processing, which are core topics in the sub-categories of cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.SP (Speech Processing), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach that operates in the parameter-space of echo locations and weights, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) that deals with off-grid signal processing.
